The '''Clackamas Country Fair and Rodeo''' is a week-long event held at the '''Clackamas County Fairgrounds''' in the city of [[Canby, Oregon|Canby]] in [[Clackamas County, Oregon|Clackamas County]], [[Oregon]], [[United States]] during the third week of August. The [[fair]] has been held yearly since 1907. Activities include [[amusement ride]]s, [[livestock]] exhibits and competitions, live entertainment on three stages, local handcraft work and produce, and a [[Professional Rodeo Cowboys Association]] (PRCA) sponsored [[rodeo]].
