'''Phlygonium''' or '''Phlygonion''' ({{lang-grc|Φλνγόνιον}}) was a city of [[ancient Phocis]] destroyed by [[Philip II of Macedon]] at the end of the [[Phocian War]] (346&nbsp;BCE).<ref>{{Cite Pausanias|10|3|2}}</ref><ref>{{Cite Stephanus|''s.v.''}}</ref> [[Pliny the Elder]] calls it '''Phlygone''', and erroneously represents it as a city of [[ancient Boeotia|Boeotia]].<ref>{{Cite Pliny|4.7.12}}</ref>

Its site is tentatively located at the Palaiokastro (old castle) near [[Ano Tseresi]].<ref>{{Cite DARE|29441}}</ref><ref>{{Cite Barrington|55}}</ref>

